                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/1258: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-27T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 27, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>673. For Pell. The Department has no objection to allowing Mr. Preuss to act as
                    alternate at meetings of Commission as suggested your 514, January 19.</p>
                <pb facs="1289" n="1275" xml:id="pg_1275"/>
                <p>Matter of dropping technical committee has not been brought to Department’s
                    attention by the British Government. Your detailed report not yet received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
